# Phase 23 Research Report — Notification Injection Architecture

## 1. Notification Architecture — `notification-handler.ts`

**Location:** `src/coordination/completion/notification-handler.ts:130-162`

**Flow:**
1. `notifyDelegationTerminal()` is called by `ProgressManager` (line ~43) when a delegation reaches terminal state.
2. Builds message via `buildNotificationMessage()` — constructs a `{ role: "assistant", parts: [{ type: "text", text: ... }] }` with notification summary.
3. Calls `sendPrompt(sessionId, message)` — the SDK wrapper at `session-api.ts:51-64` which maps to `session.prompt()` → `POST /session/{id}/message`.
4. **Critical gap:** `buildNotificationMessage()` returns a `Message` type (`{ role, parts }`), but `sendPrompt` expects a `SessionPromptData` body. The call at `notification-handler.ts:162` is `sendPrompt(sessionId, body)` where `body` is a `Message` — this works because the SDK wrapper's `sendPrompt` accepts `Omit<SessionPromptData['body'], 'parts'> & { parts: Part[] }` and coerces.

**Synthetic flag: NOT SET** — no `synthetic: true` on the text part currently.

## 2. `TextPartInput` Type Confirmation

```typescript
// node_modules/@opencode-ai/sdk/dist/gen/types.gen.d.ts:1231-1244
export type TextPartInput = {
    id?: string;
    type: "text";
    text: string;
    synthetic?: boolean;        // <-- EXISTS! ✓
    ignored?: boolean;
    time?: { start: number; end?: number };
    metadata?: { [key: string]: unknown };
};
```

**`synthetic?: boolean` is a first-class property of `TextPartInput`.** The mechanism exists in the SDK. The `sendPrompt` → `session.prompt()` → `POST /session/{id}/message` endpoint accepts this field.

## 3. `SessionPromptData` Request Shape

```typescript
// types.gen.d.ts:2244-2269
export type SessionPromptData = {
    body?: {
        messageID?: string;
        model?: { providerID: string; modelID: string };
        agent?: string;
        noReply?: boolean;
        system?: string;
        tools?: { [key: string]: boolean };
        parts: Array<TextPartInput | FilePartInput | AgentPartInput | SubtaskPartInput>;
    };
    path: { id: string };       // session ID
    url: "/session/{id}/message";
};
```

**Key points:**
- `messageID` is optional (no explicit message specified — new message created)
- `noReply?: boolean` — if `true`, the LLM does NOT respond (fire-and-forget)
- `agent?: string` — can inject into a specific agent's context
- Parts array accepts `TextPartInput` which has `synthetic`

## 4. `TuiAppendPromptData` & `TuiShowToastData`

```typescript
// types.gen.d.ts:3126-3135
export type TuiAppendPromptData = {
    body?: { text: string };
    url: "/tui/append-prompt";
};
// Response: 200 → boolean (processed successfully)

// types.gen.d.ts:3264-3279
export type TuiShowToastData = {
    body?: {
        title?: string;
        message: string;
        variant: "info" | "success" | "warning" | "error";
        duration?: number;      // in milliseconds
    };
    url: "/tui/show-toast";
};
// Response: 200 → boolean (shown successfully)
```

**Key insight:** `TuiAppendPromptData` accepts raw `{ text: string }` — no parts, no synthetic flag. This is a simple TUI-side text injection. It goes through `POST /tui/append-prompt` which the OpenCode TUI processes and the user sees as a keyboard-update simulation.

## 5. `session-api.ts` — SDK Wrapper Signatures

```typescript
// src/shared/session-api.ts (from earlier read)
sendPrompt(sessionId, body)  →  uses session.prompt({ path: { id: sessionId }, body })
appendTuiPrompt(text)        →  uses tui.appendPrompt({ body: { text } })
showTuiToast(title, message, variant, duration?)  →  uses tui.showToast({ body: { title, message, variant, duration } })
```

The wrapper currently does NOT expose `synthetic` or `agent` overrides on `sendPrompt` — they are passed through to the SDK's `SessionPromptData` body but currently not surfaced as parameters.

## 6. Injection Strategy Recommendations

### Option A: `synthetic: true` + `noReply: true` (Recommended)

**Target:** `notification-handler.ts` — in `notifyDelegationTerminal()` around line 162, when building the message parts:

```typescript
// Current:
parts: [{ type: "text", text: buildNotificationMessage(...) }]

// Target:
parts: [{ type: "text", text: buildNotificationMessage(...), synthetic: true }]
```

Additional changes needed:
- `session-api.ts` `sendPrompt()` must accept `noReply?: boolean` parameter and pass it through to `SessionPromptData.body`.
- `notification-handler.ts` `notifyDelegationTerminal()` must pass `noReply: true` so the LLM doesn't generate a response to its own notification.

**Evidence chain:**
1. `TextPartInput.synthetic` exists (line 1235) ✓
2. `SessionPromptData.body.parts` accepts `TextPartInput` (line 2257) ✓
3. `SessionPromptData.body.noReply` exists (line 2252) ✓
4. `execute-slash-command.ts:14-22` documents the synthetic parent prompt pattern (reference) ✓
5. `message-capture.ts:~356` filters out synthetic parts for session tracker — don't need to change this, it will work correctly ✓

### Option B: `appendTuiPrompt` for TUI-only notification

`notification-handler.ts` could also call `appendTuiPrompt("Delegation complete: ...")` alongside or instead of the session prompt. This is simpler (no `synthetic` flag needed) but does NOT inject into the session's message stream — it only updates the TUI's input area.

### Option C: `showTuiToast` for visible notification

A toast notification (`showTuiToast`) provides the most visible UI cue. This could be used as a supplement to either Option A or B, not as a replacement for the session message.

### Recommended Hybrid:

```
sendPrompt(sessionId, { parts: [{ type: "text", text, synthetic: true }], noReply: true })
  + appendTuiPrompt(notificationText)
```

The `sendPrompt` with `synthetic + noReply` injects the notification into the session stream (avoiding LLM reprocessing), while `appendTuiPrompt` makes it visible in the TUI. Optionally add `showTuiToast` for a visible popup.

## Key Files Summary

| File | Role | Changes Needed |
|------|------|---------------|
| `src/coordination/completion/notification-handler.ts` | Main injection point | Add `synthetic: true` + `noReply: true` |
| `src/shared/session-api.ts` | SDK wrapper | Expose `noReply` parameter on `sendPrompt()` |
| `src/coordination/completion/detector.ts` | Completion detection | No changes — detects terminal states already |
| `src/plugin.ts` | Wiring | No changes — notification already wired |
| `src/features/session-tracker/capture/message-capture.ts` | Synthetic filter | No changes — already filters `synthetic: true` parts |
| `src/tools/session/execute-slash-command.ts` | Reference pattern | No changes — read-only reference |

All evidence confirms the architecture is ready for `synthetic: true` injection. The SDK types, the session tracker filter, and the dispatch pattern all support this approach without any new SDK features or architectural changes.

